.TH wxNavigationKeyEvent 3 "wx 2.5.4" "Ericsson AB" "Erlang Module Definition"
.SH NAME
wxNavigationKeyEvent \- This event class contains information about navigation events, generated by navigation keys such as tab and page down.

.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
This event is mainly used by wxWidgets implementations. A \fIwxNavigationKeyEvent\fR handler is automatically provided by wxWidgets when you enable keyboard navigation inside a window by inheriting it from wxNavigationEnabled<>.

.PP
See: \fIwxWindow:navigate/2\fR

.PP
This class is derived, and can use functions, from:


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
.sp -1
.IP \(bu 2.3
.\}.PP
\fIwxEvent\fR

.RE

.PP
wxWidgets docs: wxNavigationKeyEvent

.SS "Events"

.PP
Use \fIwxEvtHandler:connect/3\fR with \fIwxNavigationKeyEventType\fR to subscribe to events of this type.

.SH DATA TYPES
.LP
.B
\fBwxNavigationKey() :: #wxNavigationKey{}.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxNavigationKeyEvent() :: wx:wx_object().\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.B
\fBwxNavigationKeyEventType() :: navigation_key.\fR

.br
.RS

.RE
.SH FUNCTIONS
.LP
.B
\fBgetCurrentFocus(This) -> wxWindow:wxWindow()\fR
\fB                         when This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns the child that has the focus, or NULL.


.RE
.B
\fBgetDirection(This) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                      when This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the navigation was in the forward direction.


.RE
.B
\fBisFromTab(This) -> boolean() when This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the navigation event was from a tab key.

.PP
This is required for proper navigation over radio buttons.


.RE
.B
\fBisWindowChange(This) -> boolean()\fR
\fB                        when This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Returns true if the navigation event represents a window change (for example, from Ctrl-Page Down in a notebook).


.RE
.B
\fBsetCurrentFocus(This, CurrentFocus) -> ok\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent(),\fR
\fB                             CurrentFocus :: wxWindow:wxWindow().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the current focus window member.


.RE
.B
\fBsetDirection(This, Direction) -> ok\fR
\fB                      when\fR
\fB                          This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent(),\fR
\fB                          Direction :: boolean().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Sets the direction to forward if \fIdirection\fR is true, or backward if false.


.RE
.B
\fBsetFromTab(This, FromTab) -> ok\fR
\fB                    when\fR
\fB                        This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent(),\fR
\fB                        FromTab :: boolean().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Marks the navigation event as from a tab key.


.RE
.B
\fBsetWindowChange(This, WindowChange) -> ok\fR
\fB                         when\fR
\fB                             This :: wxNavigationKeyEvent(),\fR
\fB                             WindowChange :: boolean().\fR

.br
.RS
.PP
Marks the event as a window change event.


.RE
